OBJECTIVE

Evaluate the conceptual performance of a distributed dual-module
electro-hydraulic propulsion architecture utilizing two independent VHX-220
power units synchronized by a predictive master controller.

Each propulsion module independently powers one front wheel while maintaining
continuous communication for torque balancing, traction optimization and
fault-tolerant operation.

