ENGINEERING OBSERVATIONS

• Independent propulsion at each front wheel.

• Distributed electro-hydraulic torque assistance.

• Reduced drivetrain stress through load sharing.

• Improved vehicle traction under low-grip conditions.

• Higher redundancy through duplicated propulsion modules.

• Increased thermal capacity through distributed heat generation.

• Predictive wheel torque balancing improves directional stability.

• Modular architecture simplifies maintenance and subsystem replacement.

